title: Dixie Chicks - Thank Heavens for Dale Evans
description:
This is a great record, with a lot of great harmony and, of course, talented ladies playing the heck out of just about every stringed instrument there is.
Natalie Maines, the lead singer, is witty and expressive, and her beautiful voice goes great with Martie and Emily&#039;s fiddle/banjo/mandolin/etc. Laura Lynch and Robin Lynn Macy brought some very different things to the mix, but their departures were largely, if not entirely, their own choices, and I hate to see Natalie punished for that.
